                        <h1>
                            Changes among the state secretaries</h1>
                    
                
            </div>
        </div>
    

<div class="documentBody" id="Tekstinnhold">
    
    
    
        <div>
            

<div>
	<p class="Overskrift"><strong>Following today’s changes in the Government, the King has in today’s session of the Council of State made the following changes among the state secretaries:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Mr. Torgeir Larsen, Ms. Gry Larsen, Mr. Robin Kåss, Mr. Kjell Erik Øie, Ms. Mina Gerhardsen, Ms. Kjersti Stenseng, Mr. Jan-Erik Støstad, Ms. Gina Lund and Mr. Roger Ingebrigtsen have been honourably discharged from their offices as state secretaries</li>
<li>Mr. Torgeir Larsen, state secretary, has been appointed state secretary to Minister of Foreign Affairs Espen Barth Eide</li>
<li>Ms. Gry Larsen, state secretary, has been appointed state secretary to Minister of Foreign Affairs Espen Barth Eide</li>
<li>Ms. Kristin Bergersen, acting state secretary, has been appointed state secretary to Minister of Justice and Public Security Grete Faremo</li>
<li>Mr. Roger Ingebrigtsen, state secretary, state secretary, has been appointed state secretary to Minister of Trade and Industry Trond Giske </li>
<li>Mr. Eirik Øwre Thorshaug, political adviser, has been appointed state secretary to Minister of Defence Anne-Grete Strøm-Erichsen</li>
<li>Mr. Robin Kåss, state secretary, has been appointed state secretary to Minister of Health and Care Services Jonas Gahr Støre</li>
<li>Mr. Kjell Erik Øie, state secretary, has been appointed state secretary to Minister of Health and Care Services Jonas Gahr Støre</li>
<li>Mr. Jan-Erik Støstad, state secretary, has been appointed state secretary to Minister of Labour Anniken Huitfeldt</li>
<li>Ms. Gina Lund, state secretary, has been appointed state secretary to Minister of Labour Anniken Huitfeldt</li>
<li>Ms. Mina Gerhardsen, state secretary, has been appointed state secretary to Minister of Culture Hadia Tajik</li>
<li>Ms. Kjersti Stenseng, state secretary, has been appointed state secretary to Minister of Culture Hadia Tajik</li>
</ul>
<p>The changes are active as of 3 pm today.&nbsp;</p>
<p>The Government represents the Labour Party (Lab.), the Socialist Left Party (Soc.) and the Centre Party (Cent.). The list of state secretaries is now as follows:<br /><strong><br />To Prime Minister Jens Stoltenberg</strong> (Lab.)<br />Ms. Rita Skjærvik (Lab.)<br />Mr. Tor Brostigen (Soc.) <br />Mr. Dagfinn Sundsbø (Cent.)<br />Mr. Hans Kristian Amundsen (Lab.)<br />Mr. Svein Fjellheim (Lab.)<br />Mr. Snorre Wikstrøm (Lab.) – leave of absence from 3 September 2012 <br />Ms. Inger-Anne Ravlum (Lab.)<br />Mr. Halvard Ingebrigtsen (Lab.) – acting from 24 September 2012</p>
<p><strong>To Minister of the Environment Bård Vegar Solhjell</strong> (Soc.)<br />Ms. Henriette Westhrin (Soc.)<br />Mr. Ketil Raknes (Soc.)</p>
<p><strong>To Minister of Local Government and Regional Development <br />Liv Signe Navarsete</strong> (Cent.)<br />Ms. Hege Solbakken (Cent.) <br />Mr. Dag-Henrik Sandbakken (Cent.)<br />Mr. Erlend Fuglum (Cent.)<br />Ms. Anne Beathe Kristiansen Tvinnereim (Cent.) - acting 16 January 2012-26 October 2012</p>
<p><strong>To Minister of Foreign Affairs Espen Barth Eide </strong>(Lab.)<br />Ms. Gry Larsen (Lab.)<br />Mr. Torgeir Larsen (Lab.)</p>
<p><strong>To Minister of Justice and Public Security Grete Faremo </strong>(Lab.)<br />Ms. Astri Aas-Hansen (Lab.)<br />Mr. Pål Lønseth (Lab.)<br />Ms. Kristin Bergersen (Lab.)</p>
<p><strong>To Minister of Finance Sigbjørn Johnsen</strong> (Lab.)<br />Ms. Hilde Singsaas (Lab.)<br />Mr. Kjetil Lund (Lab.)<br />Mr. Roger Schjerva (Soc.)<br />Mr. Morten Søberg (Cent.)</p>
<p><strong>To Minister of Trade and Industry Trond Giske</strong> (Lab.)<br />Mr. Roger Ingebrigtsen (Lab.) <br />Ms. Jeanette Iren Moen (Lab.) <br />Mr. Halvard Ingebrigtsen (Lab.) – acting as state secretary to Prime Minister Jens Stoltenberg from 24 September 2012</p>
<p><strong>To Minister of Defence Anne-Grete Strøm-Erichsen </strong>(Lab.)<br />Mr. Eirik Øwre Thorshaug (Lab.)</p>
<p><strong>To Minister of Health and Care Services Jonas Gahr Støre </strong>(Lab.)<br />Mr. Robin Kåss (Lab.)<br />Mr. Kjell Erik Øie (Lab.)</p>
<p><strong>To Minister of Education and Research Kristin Halvorsen</strong> (Soc.)<br />Ms. Elisabet Dahle (Soc.)<br />Ms. Ragnhild Setsaas (Soc.)</p>
<p><strong>To Minister of Labour Anniken Huitfeldt </strong>(Lab.)<br />Mr. Jan-Erik Støstad (Lab.)<br />Ms. Gina Lund (Lab.)<br /><br /><strong>To Minister of Government Administration, Reform <br />and Church Affairs Rigmor Aasrud</strong> (Lab.)<br />Ms. Tone-Helen Toften (Lab.)<br />Ms. Ragnhild Vassvik Kalstad (Lab.)</p>
<p><strong>To Minister of Fisheries and Coastal Affairs Lisbeth Berg-Hansen</strong> (Lab.)<br />Ms. Kristine Gramstad (Lab.)</p>
<p><strong>To Minister of Transport and Communications Marit Arnstad</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong> (Cent.)<br />Mr. Lars Erik Bartnes (Cent.)<br />Mr. Erik Lahnstein (Cent.)</p>
<p><strong>To Minister of Petroleum and Energy Ola Borten Moe</strong> (Cent.)<br />Ms. Eli Blakstad (Cent.)<br />Mr. Per Rune Henriksen (Lab.)</p>
<p><strong>To Minister of International Development Heikki Holmås</strong> (Soc.)<br />Mr. Arvinn Gadgil (Soc.)</p>
<p><strong>To Minister of Children, Equality and Social Inclusion<br />Inga Marte Thorkildsen</strong> (Soc.)<br />Mr. Ahmad Ghanizadeh (Soc.)<br />Mr. Kjetil Andreas Ostling (Soc.)</p>
<p><strong>To Minister of Agriculture and Food Trygve Slagsvold Vedum </strong>&nbsp;(Cent.)<br />Mr. Harald Oskar Buttedahl (Cent.)</p>
<p><strong>To Minister of Culture Hadia Tajik </strong>(Lab.)<br />Ms. Mina Gerhardsen (Lab.)<br />Ms. Kjersti Stenseng (Lab.)</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</div>
